1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
{\an8}<b><font color="#9CD5FF">One Pace Premium</font></b>
Keep the project alive: <font color="#a8c7fa">ko-fi.com/not6ip</font>

2
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:56,550
Foul Play

3
00:01:54,220 --> 00:01:56,550
Luffy!

4
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:58,560
Luffy! Luffy! Luffy! Luffy!

5
00:01:58,560 --> 00:01:59,350
Luffy! Luffy!

6
00:01:59,350 --> 00:02:02,190
Luffy!

7
00:02:05,980 --> 00:02:07,570
Ow, ow, ow...

8
00:02:08,650 --> 00:02:10,780
It's horrible! A dinosaur ate Nami!

9
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:13,780
Wait! What?!

10
00:02:12,490 --> 00:02:14,660
One moment we were
running away from it,

11
00:02:14,660 --> 00:02:18,700
and the next she had suddenly
disappeared into the jungle!

12
00:02:19,620 --> 00:02:20,830
What have I done?!

13
00:02:20,830 --> 00:02:23,460
I let my crewmate get killed!

14
00:02:24,270 --> 00:02:26,210
H-Hold on!

15
00:02:26,210 --> 00:02:28,670
Calm down, you two!

16
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:30,250
– Huh?
– Huh?

17
00:02:30,250 --> 00:02:35,300
You said she suddenly disappeared,
but did you check and make sure?

18
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,970
Are you crazy?!

19
00:02:36,970 --> 00:02:39,180
I was too terrified
to check and make sure!

20
00:02:39,180 --> 00:02:41,100
It was either a dinosaur or a beast!

21
00:02:41,100 --> 00:02:42,810
What else could it have been?!

22
00:02:42,810 --> 00:02:44,940
I don't know.

23
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:49,320
But if someone from
Baroque Works followed us here,

24
00:02:49,320 --> 00:02:53,780
then it would make sense
if Nami was taken instead of you.

25
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:55,150
What?!

26
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:58,280
Baroque Works is on the island?!

27
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,410
Wait...

28
00:03:01,290 --> 00:03:03,450
why wouldn't they go after me?

29
00:03:03,830 --> 00:03:08,380
Because there's only a slim chance
you're on their hit list.

30
00:03:08,380 --> 00:03:09,420
Makes sense!

31
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:14,700
Plus, we were probably supposed
to drink that alcohol too!

32
00:03:15,380 --> 00:03:16,380
Alcohol?!

33
00:03:16,380 --> 00:03:18,510
What alcohol?!

34
00:03:18,510 --> 00:03:21,850
Brogy brought your alcohol to Dorry,

35
00:03:21,850 --> 00:03:26,980
and when Dorry drank it,
it exploded inside his stomach.

36
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:29,860
What?! Our alcohol exploded
inside his stomach?!

37
00:03:30,610 --> 00:03:33,990
You're saying he continued
the duel all busted up like that?!

38
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:37,070
And when I tried to stop him,
this is what he did to me.

39
00:03:39,490 --> 00:03:41,330
You can't be serious!

40
00:03:41,330 --> 00:03:47,750
Those two have fought on equal ground
for 100 years with all their might!

41
00:03:52,380 --> 00:03:56,340
It's gotta be the most honorable battle
ever fought in this world!

42
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:56,920
Yeah...

43
00:03:56,920 --> 00:04:00,010
They can't settle the fight
like this now!

44
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:04,270
What's wrong?!

45
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:17,860
He's still fighting.

46
00:04:18,910 --> 00:04:22,990
Yes. Dorry the Blue Ogre
is quite stubborn indeed.

47
00:04:24,870 --> 00:04:27,620
Perhaps I should lend a hand.

48
00:04:38,970 --> 00:04:41,180
One century...

49
00:04:45,770 --> 00:04:49,690
It was a long battle!

50
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:31,140
Heaven has censured me.

51
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:33,980
Elbaph, the god of war,
has decided my fate.

52
00:05:33,980 --> 00:05:36,480
I didn't have his divine protection.

53
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,400
That is all.

54
00:05:46,120 --> 00:05:46,950
Luffy!

55
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,040
Luffy?!

56
00:05:48,410 --> 00:05:51,620
Who was it?!

57
00:05:51,620 --> 00:06:02,550
Show yourself!

58
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:04,680
Huh?

59
00:06:05,550 --> 00:06:08,350
Mr. 3, I think I heard something.

60
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:12,270
How amusing!

61
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:14,980
An underdog also-ran,
yelping out here in the jungle!

62
00:06:20,940 --> 00:06:24,320
Seventy-three... thousand...

63
00:06:26,030 --> 00:06:30,200
four hundred... sixty-seven duels.

64
00:06:32,250 --> 00:06:38,210
Seventy-three... thousand...
four hundred sixty-six draws...

65
00:06:41,050 --> 00:06:42,720
and one win!

66
00:06:58,650 --> 00:07:00,820
Tears of joy over your victory?

67
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:02,990
Simpletons have it so easy.

68
00:07:03,820 --> 00:07:07,110
Though, I suppose
congratulations are in order.

69
00:07:07,110 --> 00:07:09,080
Tears of joy?!

70
00:07:09,080 --> 00:07:11,450
What would you know?!

71
00:07:11,450 --> 00:07:12,870
Just who are you?!

72
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:14,710
Mr. 3.

73
00:07:14,710 --> 00:07:19,380
Please excuse the code name.
I'm a mere formative artist.

74
00:07:19,380 --> 00:07:25,340
And this is my assistant
and realist painter, Miss Golden Week.

75
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:29,800
What's more,
I've already captured you.

76
00:07:31,560 --> 00:07:33,980
Wh-What is this?!

77
00:07:40,770 --> 00:07:42,110
Alright, Luffy!

78
00:07:42,110 --> 00:07:45,490
I dunno who we're dealing with,
but I'll go take care of them myself!

79
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,490
I'll come with you!

80
00:07:47,490 --> 00:07:50,780
Yes! If you insist!
I wouldn't mind the backup!

81
00:07:50,780 --> 00:07:52,370
There's no need for that!

82
00:07:55,370 --> 00:07:56,830
You guys again!

83
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:06,170
You can have him back.

84
00:08:06,170 --> 00:08:07,170
We don't need him.

85
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:10,470
Karoo!

86
00:08:10,470 --> 00:08:12,600
Why, you...!

87
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,270
Hey, who are they?

88
00:08:14,270 --> 00:08:15,980
They're from that last town!

89
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:18,100
What are you doing here?!

90
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:19,980
Karoo has nothing to do with this!

91
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:23,860
That's right. The bird has
absolutely nothing to do with this.

92
00:08:23,860 --> 00:08:28,900
The only one we considered
a threat was that straw hat guy.

93
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:36,620
The plan was to make the bird squawk
to lure you away from him,

94
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:39,080
but that is one obstinate duck.

95
00:08:39,920 --> 00:08:42,670
Now, then! Call for your owner!

96
00:08:44,130 --> 00:08:47,090
Quack especially loud,
and we'll let you go free!

97
00:08:51,090 --> 00:08:53,550
Fine! Want us to make you quack?!

98
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:56,220
Call for the princess!

99
00:08:59,890 --> 00:09:01,730
Call for help...

100
00:09:01,730 --> 00:09:03,980
this instant!

101
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:09,490
Open your mouth, you damn bird!

102
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:16,490
But it looks like Straw Hat's
already out of the picture.

103
00:09:16,490 --> 00:09:18,700
So the duck's no use to us now.

104
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:20,460
Karoo...

105
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:27,340
What a stupid bird!

106
00:09:29,630 --> 00:09:31,840
Why, you...!

107
00:09:31,840 --> 00:09:35,180
Are you the ones
who made the alcohol explode?!

108
00:09:36,180 --> 00:09:39,060
Yes, that was us, but who are you?

109
00:09:39,060 --> 00:09:40,060
Is he on the list?

110
00:09:40,060 --> 00:09:43,520
No, but he seems to be a shipmate.
Let's make him disappear too!

111
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:46,400
So, you interfered
with the giants' duel!

112
00:09:46,770 --> 00:09:48,440
It was them?!

113
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:49,900
I'll kick their asses!

114
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,360
You're the ones who'll disappear!

115
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:57,370
Oh? You're gonna
start something, Miss Wednesday?

116
00:09:58,830 --> 00:10:02,410
What makes you think
you're a match for officer agents?

117
00:10:02,410 --> 00:10:04,420
Peacock Slasher!

118
00:10:04,420 --> 00:10:05,170
Take this!

119
00:10:05,170 --> 00:10:07,250
Lethal Exploding Star!

120
00:10:10,550 --> 00:10:11,380
Bull's-eye!

121
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,930
Nice updraft!

122
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:18,510
Nose Fancy Cannon!

123
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:25,440
Pitiful man!

124
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:27,020
Usopp!

125
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:28,980
10,000 Kilo Press!

126
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:35,490
Give it a rest!

127
00:10:42,160 --> 00:10:43,790
Why so agitated?

128
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:46,750
We're not gonna kill you just yet.

129
00:10:50,750 --> 00:10:53,090
We only came to capture you.

130
00:10:53,090 --> 00:10:55,590
All per Mr. 3's orders.

131
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,760
Mr. 3?!

132
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,520
The Wax-Wax Fruit man?!

133
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:03,180
He's on this island?!

134
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:05,060
That's right.

135
00:11:05,060 --> 00:11:10,690
He's a candle man who controls
wax secreted from his body.

136
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:16,160
You wretch!

137
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:17,570
What is all this?!

138
00:11:19,370 --> 00:11:21,200
Isn't it obvious?

139
00:11:21,200 --> 00:11:24,370
This is why I can't stand
unsophisticated dolts.

140
00:11:24,370 --> 00:11:28,580
I'm creating a work of art, obviously.

141
00:11:34,010 --> 00:11:36,260
Just be a good little girl.

142
00:11:36,260 --> 00:11:41,470
Did you honestly think you could
escape from Baroque Works?

143
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:52,520
Even that guy with the bounty
of 30 million was no match for us.

144
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:56,990
I can finally return the favor
for Whisky Peak.

145
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:59,490
You wannabe pirates had it coming

146
00:11:59,490 --> 00:12:03,120
for sticking your noses
into such a sensitive operation.

147
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:08,420
We've already captured your
swordsman friend and the other girl.

148
00:12:09,330 --> 00:12:11,000
You caught Zoro?

149
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:11,880
Huh?

150
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:14,630
Then you guys are dead meat!

151
00:12:14,630 --> 00:12:15,880
Oh?

152
00:12:15,880 --> 00:12:17,880
You talk awfully big...

153
00:12:17,880 --> 00:12:20,800
for a guy who received one of my
Kicky Bombs to the face.

154
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:23,180
Those don't hurt one bit!

155
00:12:23,180 --> 00:12:25,600
I'm gonna kick all your asses!

156
00:12:29,730 --> 00:12:30,810
Pitiful.

157
00:12:34,150 --> 00:12:35,400
Luffy!

158
00:12:38,570 --> 00:12:39,660
Die!

159
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:53,420
Chump!

160
00:12:53,420 --> 00:12:55,050
Luffy!

161
00:12:55,050 --> 00:12:57,720
Luffy! Luffy!

162
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:59,300
Let's go, Miss Valentine.

163
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:00,510
Luffy!

164
00:13:01,390 --> 00:13:03,470
Usopp! Karoo!

165
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:25,580
Damn you!

166
00:13:25,990 --> 00:13:28,500
Give it up! Give it up!

167
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:34,290
Once solidified, my candle jacket
is as hard as steel!

168
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:38,210
You giants may have brutish strength,

169
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:42,430
but you're weak when
compared to these bonds.

170
00:13:42,430 --> 00:13:44,760
Brainpower wins out in the end.

171
00:13:44,760 --> 00:13:47,600
I won't stoop to needlessly
face you head-on.

172
00:13:48,470 --> 00:13:51,350
Upon tasting victory,
you lowered your guard,

173
00:13:51,350 --> 00:13:53,230
Brogy the Red Ogre.

174
00:13:55,610 --> 00:13:57,440
Don't glare at me like that.

175
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:59,530
You're so terrifying!

176
00:14:00,740 --> 00:14:02,910
You should be thrilled!

177
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:06,740
The duel has finally arrived
at its long-awaited end.

178
00:14:06,740 --> 00:14:11,080
Didn't you fight for a whole century
with your so-called pride on the line?

179
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:14,920
Shouldn't the taste of victory
be especially sweet, then?

180
00:14:14,920 --> 00:14:18,960
Even if the fruit is borne
of another's assistance?

181
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,260
Do you disagree?

182
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:22,840
You didn't...!

183
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:23,970
You didn't...!

184
00:14:27,510 --> 00:14:29,100
But indeed!

185
00:14:29,100 --> 00:14:31,230
The final victory belongs to me!

186
00:14:31,230 --> 00:14:36,480
Were you aware that your massive,
long-standing bounties

187
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,230
amounted to 200 million berries?

188
00:14:38,230 --> 00:14:40,690
Today, that is still the case.

189
00:14:41,690 --> 00:14:42,900
You scum!

190
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:46,870
I feel as if I've stumbled upon
a long-lost treasure!

191
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:49,910
So that's what you're after, huh?!

192
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:50,490
Hmm?

193
00:14:50,490 --> 00:14:52,000
Mr. 3!

194
00:14:52,790 --> 00:14:54,000
Here she is.

195
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:56,790
Our company's little traitor.

196
00:14:56,790 --> 00:14:57,960
What took so long?

197
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,500
I was getting sick of waiting.

198
00:14:59,500 --> 00:15:02,460
Your underhanded scheme
went too far, Mr. 3!

199
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:05,840
You arranged for Dorry's
alcohol to explode!

200
00:15:05,840 --> 00:15:06,970
What?!

201
00:15:07,720 --> 00:15:08,930
Alcohol?

202
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:12,310
The drink I gave to him...
That alcohol?!

203
00:15:14,850 --> 00:15:15,890
Dorry!

204
00:15:15,890 --> 00:15:18,270
How was your drink?!
Hit the spot, didn't it?!

205
00:15:18,770 --> 00:15:20,070
Yeah.

206
00:15:20,070 --> 00:15:22,530
Truly the nectar of the gods.

207
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:26,110
So, that's what you meant, Dorry?!

208
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:30,530
Wretched girl,
giving away company secrets.

209
00:15:30,530 --> 00:15:31,950
Not that it matters.

210
00:15:31,950 --> 00:15:34,500
You're helpless now, after all.

211
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:39,000
Candle...

212
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,670
Lock!

213
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:50,350
Mr. 5!

214
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:51,050
Huh?

215
00:15:51,050 --> 00:15:52,850
Bring the swordsman and the girl!

216
00:15:54,350 --> 00:15:55,230
Let us commence.

217
00:15:59,060 --> 00:16:04,650
Extra-Large Candle Set!

218
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:31,260
What's going on?!

219
00:16:32,050 --> 00:16:33,720
Here they are.

220
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:40,190
Disgraceful.

221
00:16:42,020 --> 00:16:45,150
Getting bested by these lowlifes
was beyond embarrassing.

222
00:16:45,150 --> 00:16:47,820
I'm disgusted with myself.

223
00:16:48,320 --> 00:16:49,610
What is that?!

224
00:16:49,610 --> 00:16:52,070
Nami... Mr. Bushido...

225
00:16:52,070 --> 00:16:53,080
Vivi!

226
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:55,740
What happened?!
Weren't you with Luffy?!

227
00:16:55,740 --> 00:16:57,450
Yes, I was, but–

228
00:16:57,450 --> 00:17:01,380
If you mean Straw Hat,
I took him out myself!

229
00:17:02,630 --> 00:17:04,960
And I didn't even break a sweat.

230
00:17:05,550 --> 00:17:06,960
You?

231
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:27,990
Welcome, one and all,
to my service set!

232
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:35,950
Is this how it feels
to be a candle stuck in a cake?

233
00:17:35,950 --> 00:17:38,910
What's that spinning thing up there?

234
00:17:40,710 --> 00:17:42,290
And I can't move my legs.

235
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:45,960
Makes sense for them
to keep us immobilized.

236
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:47,300
They're the enemy.

237
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:52,840
Too hard.

238
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:56,760
And I can't get a solid hit on it
from this stance.

239
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,640
Huh?! Something's raining down!

240
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:04,020
I hope you enjoy my candle service!

241
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:07,150
The wax particles
settling down on you

242
00:18:07,150 --> 00:18:09,990
will soon transform you
into wax sculptures!

243
00:18:10,860 --> 00:18:14,070
You'll become perfect
models of humankind,

244
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:17,030
such that my skills alone
could not achieve!

245
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:22,000
Your wax figures will have
literally captured your spirit!

246
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:25,000
Now, in the name of art...

247
00:18:25,330 --> 00:18:26,960
perish.

248
00:18:27,630 --> 00:18:29,550
Screw that!

249
00:18:29,550 --> 00:18:32,970
Why do we have to become
your works of art?!

250
00:18:33,470 --> 00:18:36,300
Brogy! Get back up
and crush these maniacs!

251
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:39,100
You'll turn into
a wax statue too, you know!

252
00:18:39,100 --> 00:18:41,600
Man, that's a huge person.

253
00:18:42,810 --> 00:18:46,100
Nothing you say
will move him to action!

254
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:52,820
Despite a proud victory, he's realized
the absurdity of his tears of joy.

255
00:18:52,820 --> 00:18:56,570
He slew his friend Dorry,
with whom he fought for 100 years,

256
00:18:56,570 --> 00:19:04,250
but he utterly failed to notice
the injuries Dorry had already sustained!

257
00:19:04,250 --> 00:19:08,040
Or, perhaps, were you actually
mourning your dear friend?

258
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:13,420
Whatever the case, there's no
turning back the hands of time, you fool!

259
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,350
I knew...

260
00:19:25,350 --> 00:19:26,600
Huh?

261
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:29,310
I knew about it.

262
00:19:34,650 --> 00:19:37,450
From the moment
we resumed our duel,

263
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:40,080
I knew Dorry was hiding something.

264
00:19:40,450 --> 00:19:43,250
Oh? You knew, huh?

265
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:44,120
A likely story!

266
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:47,540
If so, then why didn't you
call off the duel?

267
00:19:47,540 --> 00:19:53,340
Anyone could see there was
no restraint in your killing blow!

268
00:19:56,930 --> 00:19:59,590
A coward who knows
nothing of the valor of battle...

269
00:19:59,590 --> 00:20:02,470
would never understand
the truth behind my tears!

270
00:20:03,350 --> 00:20:05,930
And how could you know?!

271
00:20:05,930 --> 00:20:10,270
Are you suggesting that I dishonor
a warrior who hides his injuries

272
00:20:10,270 --> 00:20:11,730
and does battle anyway?!

273
00:20:15,650 --> 00:20:22,080
A wounded warrior who chooses
to keep fighting asks not for mercy!

274
00:20:23,030 --> 00:20:26,000
And now, I know the reason behind it.

275
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:30,960
With that knowledge, I will settle this
using my own two hands!

276
00:20:39,590 --> 00:20:41,510
That's the very least I can do...

277
00:20:41,510 --> 00:20:43,890
to honor my dear friend Dorry!

278
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:49,640
Brogy!

279
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:57,320
– Brogy!
– Brogy!

280
00:20:58,110 --> 00:21:00,320
What an annoying, talkative monster.

281
00:21:01,740 --> 00:21:05,240
U... Usopp...

282
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:06,910
Usopp...!

283
00:21:09,870 --> 00:21:13,130
You gonna let them...
get away with this?

284
00:21:13,590 --> 00:21:15,000
No...

285
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,590
I won't.

286
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:28,430
Are you... angry too?

287
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:37,030
Alright! Let's all three of us...

288
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:39,780
go kick their asses!

289
00:21:39,780 --> 00:21:40,900
Brogy!

290
00:21:41,910 --> 00:21:42,740
What a halfwit!

291
00:21:43,990 --> 00:21:49,450
I underestimated the brutish
strength of these giants!

292
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:54,630
It's clear now that simply
restraining you won't be enough!

293
00:21:54,630 --> 00:21:57,590
Wax-Wax Arts: Handcuffs!

294
00:22:00,760 --> 00:22:02,220
I'm just getting started!

295
00:22:08,770 --> 00:22:11,430
And now for the pièce de résistance!

296
00:22:11,430 --> 00:22:12,480
Take this!

297
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:24,870
Just try to move now, will you?!

298
00:22:33,460 --> 00:22:35,420
How can he be so cruel?

299
00:22:35,420 --> 00:22:38,380
And now, accelerate, candle service!

300
00:22:39,050 --> 00:22:43,090
Turn these people into wax figures!

301
00:22:48,260 --> 00:22:50,270
M-My chest is starting to burn.

302
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:52,480
The wax mist is getting into our lungs!

303
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:55,850
At this rate, we'll turn into
wax statues from the inside out!

304
00:22:57,150 --> 00:22:58,480
Yes! Yes!

305
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:01,820
The more pained you look, the better!

306
00:23:02,190 --> 00:23:07,820
Expressions of pain and agony
are the very things I seek in art!

307
00:23:08,780 --> 00:23:10,830
Solidify while filled with terror!

308
00:23:11,370 --> 00:23:13,960
You call this art,
you creepy topknot freak?!

309
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:17,170
And how dare you do that to Brogy!

310
00:23:17,960 --> 00:23:21,050
This'll come back to bite you
in the ass! You hear?!

311
00:23:23,210 --> 00:23:25,550
Scream and shout
as much as you want!

312
00:23:32,140 --> 00:23:33,600
For 100 years...

313
00:23:42,070 --> 00:23:46,530
day in and day out,
we fought and fought.

314
00:23:46,530 --> 00:23:52,040
We dueled to maintain our pride
as warriors of Elbaph!

315
00:23:52,660 --> 00:23:53,660
So then,

316
00:23:53,660 --> 00:23:58,710
how is this what you promised,
Elbaph, god of war?!

317
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:06,680
If this is how we are
to meet our end, Elbaph,

318
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:08,840
do we not deserve better?!

319
00:24:08,840 --> 00:24:13,140
Should we not die in battle?!

320
00:24:15,770 --> 00:24:17,810
What a splendid expression!

321
00:24:17,810 --> 00:24:21,150
Yes! That sorrow!
That grief! That struggle!

322
00:24:21,150 --> 00:24:24,610
What a marvelous work of art!

323
00:24:24,610 --> 00:24:27,030
Elbaph!

324
00:24:27,570 --> 00:24:29,660
Oh no! My hands won't move!

325
00:24:29,660 --> 00:24:32,160
I don't wanna die this way!
Can't we do something?!

326
00:24:32,160 --> 00:24:34,370
My body's already becoming stiff!

327
00:24:34,370 --> 00:24:35,950
What do we do?!

328
00:24:36,580 --> 00:24:38,710
Z-Zoro! Do something!

329
00:24:39,420 --> 00:24:41,040
Hey, old-timer.

330
00:24:41,380 --> 00:24:42,880
You can still move, can't you?

331
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:43,800
Huh?

332
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:45,460
So can I.

333
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:50,760
How about you and I...
crush these guys?

334
00:24:52,430 --> 00:24:54,100
Hold on, Zoro! What are you doing?!

335
00:24:54,100 --> 00:24:55,220
You're not seriously–

336
00:24:55,220 --> 00:24:55,930
Yeah.

337
00:24:55,930 --> 00:24:58,270
Don't joke about
cutting off your legs!

338
00:24:58,270 --> 00:25:00,190
It's not a joke.

339
00:25:00,190 --> 00:25:02,690
It's the only way outta here.

340
00:25:02,690 --> 00:25:03,770
And you two?

341
00:25:03,770 --> 00:25:05,280
What about us?! It's futile!

342
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,900
Even if you escape,
they'll just catch you again!

343
00:25:08,320 --> 00:25:10,860
There's no way to know that
unless we try!

344
00:25:11,490 --> 00:25:14,620
After all, we're gonna
kick the bucket if we stay here.

345
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:16,830
Instead, let's put up
one hell of a struggle!

346
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:21,080
I'm not gonna lie down
and die for this scum!

347
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:22,330
Right?!

348
00:25:22,330 --> 00:25:24,500
What the hell? Is he crazy?

349
00:25:25,090 --> 00:25:26,590
A mere bluff!

350
00:25:26,590 --> 00:25:28,800
What he's threatening
to do is ludicrous!

351
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:30,300
It's all an act!

352
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:36,220
You're pretty cocky, kiddo.

353
00:25:36,220 --> 00:25:37,810
How embarrassing.

354
00:25:37,810 --> 00:25:40,730
I had just about lost the will to fight.

355
00:25:41,350 --> 00:25:44,190
But your fiery spirit
has me raring to go!

356
00:25:46,110 --> 00:25:48,360
You can't be serious, right?!

357
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,610
How will you fight once you're free?!

358
00:25:50,610 --> 00:25:51,570
Who knows?

359
00:25:51,950 --> 00:25:53,070
But...

360
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:55,740
I plan to win.

361
00:25:56,530 --> 00:25:58,200
What's with these guys?!

362
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,750
They're off their rockers!

363
00:26:00,370 --> 00:26:02,250
What kind of man is he?!

364
00:26:02,250 --> 00:26:06,380
Still, I've seen this look
somewhere before...

365
00:26:06,380 --> 00:26:07,710
Princess Vivi!

366
00:26:08,170 --> 00:26:11,170
Are you resolved to stay alive?

367
00:26:11,170 --> 00:26:12,510
W-Wait!

368
00:26:12,510 --> 00:26:13,680
I'll fight, too!

369
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:14,300
Vivi!

370
00:26:14,300 --> 00:26:15,640
Good to hear.

371
00:26:16,050 --> 00:26:19,390
Let's do it, kiddo!

372
00:26:19,390 --> 00:26:22,390
Ridiculous! Do you even
have a plan of attack?!

373
00:26:32,610 --> 00:26:33,910
Hey, you guys!

374
00:26:33,910 --> 00:26:35,870
Get ready to get your asses kicked!

375
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:40,410
What?

376
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:43,290
Let's do it, Usopp!

377
00:26:43,290 --> 00:26:43,920
Yeah!

378
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:45,540
Bird?!

379
00:26:45,540 --> 00:26:46,460
Luffy!

380
00:26:46,460 --> 00:26:47,420
Usopp!

381
00:26:47,790 --> 00:26:48,550
Karoo!

382
00:26:48,920 --> 00:26:52,800
Master Brogy!
Your anger is now our own!

383
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:53,720
Usopp...!

384
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:56,720
Beat those guys beyond recognition

385
00:26:56,720 --> 00:26:58,890
and send them flying
far away from here!

386
00:26:58,890 --> 00:27:00,180
Yeah! I will!

387
00:27:00,810 --> 00:27:04,690
They spoiled the duel
the old giant guys were having!

388
00:27:05,060 --> 00:27:09,690
Do you really have
the highest bounty in the East Blue?

389
00:27:09,690 --> 00:27:12,360
My, how Marine Headquarters'
standards have fallen!

390
00:27:12,360 --> 00:27:13,990
Whoa! That hair is weird!

391
00:27:13,990 --> 00:27:14,860
Shut your mouth!

392
00:27:14,860 --> 00:27:16,740
It's a burning number three!

393
00:27:16,740 --> 00:27:17,370
Shut it!

394
00:27:17,370 --> 00:27:20,330
Break this pillar first, Luffy!

395
00:27:20,330 --> 00:27:22,870
We're about to turn into wax figures!

396
00:27:22,870 --> 00:27:23,540
Huh?

397
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:25,250
Oh? You're in trouble?

398
00:27:25,250 --> 00:27:27,040
Nope. No trouble here.

399
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:29,040
Hey, wait! Your legs!

400
00:27:29,040 --> 00:27:29,790
Yeah.

401
00:27:30,170 --> 00:27:32,130
I got about halfway
through them, I'd say.

402
00:27:32,130 --> 00:27:35,220
How can you say that's "no trouble"?!

403
00:27:35,590 --> 00:27:39,390
Like she said, could you
bust this pillar for us, Luffy?

404
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:41,180
After that, go wild.

405
00:27:41,890 --> 00:27:43,350
Yeah, sure thing!

406
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:46,270
I wouldn't be so sure.

407
00:27:46,770 --> 00:27:50,060
I don't know what it is,
but we're gonna break it!

408
00:27:50,060 --> 00:27:51,270
Oh, yeah!

409
00:27:51,270 --> 00:27:52,480
Got it!

410
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:55,400
I'm not the same man as before!

411
00:27:58,070 --> 00:28:01,160
Hurry before we turn solid!
